verbose_text: Interestingly, compared to macrophages derived from 36-month-old WT mice, the age matched GH-R-deficient BMDMs showed reduced caspase-1 activation and active p17 subunit response to canonical NLRP3 ligands ATP, urate crystals, and ROS damage induced by sodium arsenite (XREF_FIG).
